<br>
2 – Walkers are honest, fair and considerate, both in their dealings with each other and with outsiders. Being a Walker means you have inherited a good reputation, one that will open doors for you throughout Norrath and Luclin. Keep the guild's name at least as good as it was when you received it.<br>
<br>
3 – You are your own person. You are never required to attend a guild raid, meeting or election. You are never required to offer another Walker assistance, whether it is in the form of coinage, equipment, military aid, healing spells, curing spells, resurrections or teleports. However, you will normally find these freely offered to you and your willingness to do the same is appreciated. Likewise, the guild is strongest when we stand together; attendance at meetings and elections is greatly appreciated.<br>
<br>
4 – All Walkers are equal, and have an equal vote in decisions, with majority rule deciding all issues unless stated otherwise.<br>
<br>
5 – New members must be nominated by three current guild members who vouch that they know the prospective member and have grouped with them. A vote then follows, with a minimum of 10 Walkers voting their approval. A one week period calling for objections then follows. A current member may veto a nomination to which they are violently opposed by throwing a blackball. However, such a move requires an explanation of their reasons.<br>
<br>
6 – The leader of the Walkers is elected by a simple majority of the membership once every three months, on the first Saturday of March, June, September and December. The leader can also be voted out at any time if 50 percent of the total membership votes to do so.<br>
<br>
7 – Officers in the Walkers are a purely ceremonial position, and officership is given by the leader as a recognition of a leadership role the member has already taken on.<br>
<br>
8 – Walkers have an absolute right to personal privacy – if you know something personal about another member, keep it to yourself.<br>
<br>
9 – We are presently allied with the Coldain Dwarves of Velious and the dragons known as the Claws of Veeshan. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub78.ezboard.com/uwhizbangdustyboots.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Whizbang Dustyboots</A> at: 6/6/02 3:29:42 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub78.ezboard.com/fwalkersofvazaellefrm7.threadControl?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub78.ezboard.com/fwalkersofvazaellefrm7.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub78.ezboard.com/fwalkersofvazaellefrm7.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub78.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="walkersofvazaellefrm4">General<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm10">Screenshots<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm19">Polling Station<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm23">Computer and Technical Issues<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm7">Charter<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm8">Guides<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm3">Private<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm2">Raids<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm15">Epics<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm11">Membership<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm20">Guild Policy Discussion<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm17">Guild Vault<option value="walkersofvazaellefrm26">Whizbang's Vault</select></td><td><input type=submit val